ðŸ”¹ Aim

To build a Weather Station using ESP8266 and DHT11/DHT22 sensor that shows Temperature and Humidity on a webpage using Wi-Fi.

ðŸ”¹ Components Required

ESP8266 (NodeMCU / Wemos D1 Mini) â€“ 1

DHT11 or DHT22 Sensor â€“ 1

Breadboard â€“ 1

Jumper wires â€“ few

USB cable â€“ 1

ðŸ”¹ Circuit Connections

DHT VCC â†’ ESP8266 3.3V

DHT GND â†’ ESP8266 GND

DHT Data â†’ ESP8266 D4 (GPIO2)

ðŸ”¹ Working Principle

The DHT sensor measures temperature and humidity.

The ESP8266 connects to Wi-Fi and creates a web server.

The data is displayed on a webpage, which can be viewed on any phone or computer connected to the same Wi-Fi.
ðŸ”¹ Full Arduino Code
*********************************************************************************************************************************
#include <ESP8266WiFi.h>
#include "DHT.h"

#define DHTPIN D4        // Pin connected to DHT sensor
#define DHTTYPE DHT11    // Use DHT22 if using that sensor

DHT dht(DHTPIN, DHTTYPE);

const char* ssid = "YOUR_WIFI_SSID";      // Replace with your Wi-Fi name
const char* password = "YOUR_WIFI_PASS";  // Replace with your Wi-Fi password

WiFiServer server(80);

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  dht.begin();

  // Connect to Wi-Fi
  WiFi.begin(ssid, password);
  Serial.print("Connecting to Wi-Fi");
  while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) {
    delay(500);
    Serial.print(".");
  }
  Serial.println("\nConnected!");
  Serial.print("IP address: ");
  Serial.println(WiFi.localIP()); // This IP will be used in browser

  server.begin();
}

void loop() {
  WiFiClient client = server.available();
  if (!client) return;

  while (!client.available()) delay(1);

  client.readStringUntil('\r');  // Read HTTP request
  client.flush();

  float h = dht.readHumidity();
  float t = dht.readTemperature();

  // Build webpage
  String html = "<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset='UTF-8'><title>Weather Station</title>";
  html += "<style>body{font-family:Arial;text-align:center;background:#eef;}h1{color:#333;}p{font-size:22px;}</style>";
  html += "</head><body>";
  html += "<h1>ðŸŒ¦ ESP8266 Weather Station</h1>";
  html += "<p><b>Temperature:</b> " + String(t) + " Â°C</p>";
  html += "<p><b>Humidity:</b> " + String(h) + " %</p>";
  html += "</body></html>";

  // Send response
  client.println("HTTP/1.1 200 OK");
  client.println("Content-type:text/html");
  client.println();
  client.println(html);
  client.stop();
}
****************************************************************************************************************************************
ðŸ”¹ How to Run

Upload the code to ESP8266.

Open Serial Monitor â†’ Note the IP address (example: 192.168.1.45).

Open Chrome/Browser â†’ Type:

http://192.168.1.45


The webpage will show Temperature and Humidity.

